  "prompt": "What is a boy/girl called when he/she is 1-6 years old, 6-11years old, 11-14 years old, and 14-18 years old?",
  "response": "The stages of childhood and adolescence are generally categorized as follows:\n\n1. **1-6 years old**: Children in this age range are typically referred to as \"toddlers\" (particularly from 1-3 years) and \"preschoolers\" (around 3-5 years). By the age of 5 or 6, they might be referred to as \"early school-age children.\"\n\n2. **6-11 years old**: This age group is often called \"school-age children\" or \"middle childhood.\" They are sometimes referred to as \"grade schoolers,\" as these are the primary years for elementary education.\n\n3. **11-14 years old**: This period is known as \"early adolescence\" or \"tweens\" (particularly around 10-12 years) and \"young adolescents.\" By 13 or 14, they are typically referred to as \"teenagers.\"\n\n4. **14-18 years old**: Individuals in this range are usually called \"teenagers\" or \"adolescents.\" This stage, which includes high school years for many, is characterized by continued development and transition to adulthood.\n\nThese age categories can vary slightly depending on context and culture, but they generally align with the developmental stages commonly recognized.",
